# Azure DevOps — pipelines on Azure Repos `dev`

Pipelines are wired to **Azure Repos**, not GitHub `origin`. Integration branch is **`dev`** (not **`main`**): **`git push origin dev`** is mandatory so **`origin/dev`** stays current; Azure product mirrors are **additional** (they also target Azure branch **`dev`**).

| Folder in this monorepo | Azure DevOps repo |
|-------------------------|-------------------|
| `apps/alert-theleetclub-com/` | `https://dev.azure.com/leetclub/Leet%20Monitor/_git/alert` |
| `monitoring-app-v2/` | `https://dev.azure.com/leetclub/Leet%20Monitor/_git/monitoring-app-v2` |
| `people-analytics-sync/` | `https://dev.azure.com/leetclub/Leet%20Monitor/_git/people-analytics-sync` |

## Mandatory for the agent (unless the user says **skip push**)

After commits that should go to GitHub and Azure:

1. **`git status` / `git add` / `git commit`** on branch **`dev`** (or merge into **`dev`** before pushing — do **not** treat **`main`** as the default publish branch unless the user explicitly asked for **`main`**).

2. **Mirror every product repo that has new commits** (not just one folder). From repo root in **WSL**:

   ```bash
   bash scripts/sync-changed-azure-repos.sh
   ```

   This compares **`merge-base(origin/dev, HEAD)..HEAD`** (override with **`AZURE_SYNC_UPSTREAM`** only if the repo truly uses another ref) and runs **`sync-to-azure-dev.sh`** for **each** of **alert**, **monitoring-app-v2**, and **people-analytics-sync** whose paths appear in that diff. **Do not** sync only alert when people-api or v2 also changed in the same batch.

   Run **`before`** **`git push origin dev`** so unpushed commits are still visible to the script. Details: **`azure-repos-sync-from-monorepo.mdc`**.

3. **Push GitHub branch `dev`**, not **`main`**: **`git push origin dev`** when your checked-out branch is **`dev`**; if you are temporarily on another branch but the work belongs on **`dev`**, use **`git push origin HEAD:dev`**. Never default to **`git push origin main`** for routine code updates.

4. **Manual / recovery:** To force one tree without relying on commit detection:

   ```bash
   bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh alert apps/alert-theleetclub-com
   bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh monitoring-app-v2 monitoring-app-v2
   bash scripts/sync-to-azure-dev.sh people-analytics-sync people-analytics-sync
   ```

   Use if **`sync-changed-azure-repos.sh`** skipped a path you still need (e.g. you already pushed and the diff vs **`origin/dev`** is empty).

5. **Pipelines:** Azure **`dev`** is what **`azure-pipelines.yml`** triggers on in each Azure repo — **not** **`main`**.

6. **Do not treat `git push origin dev` alone as “Azure / CI done”.** Conversely, **do not** skip **`git push origin dev`** after a successful Azure sync.

7. **Fallback (slow):** If **`sync-to-azure-dev.sh`** cannot be used, **`bash scripts/push-to-azure-repos.sh`** (`git subtree push`) is a last resort.

8. If either push fails: print the **exact** error (no credentials). PAT: **`azure.txt`** / **`scripts/ado-curl-auth.sh`** — **do not** paste tokens in chat.

**Do not** run `docker` / `kubectl` for these products unless the user explicitly asks.

Legacy GAS (`monitoring-app-v1/`) still follows **`deploy-gas-and-people-api.mdc`** where applicable.
